3 Compressed files
******************

InfView supports compressed info files. For that they must have one of the
following extentions `igz', `gz', `info.gz' or `inz'.  Additionally they
must be compressed with GNU's gzip and gzip must be installed in your
system and in your search path.

Compressing the files under Linux or Windows 95 (with LFN=Y) is relative
easy because you only need to compress the files and they will have the
`gz' extention added. Under plain DOS is a little  harder because a file
called `file.i10' will become `file.i1z' and will have the same name as a
compressed file that had the following name `file.i1'. To fix that you
must first rename the files to have the following format: `file.nn'.  Then
you must edit the first file to fix the `Indirect' table to reflect the
changes.


